<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="224" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d224">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Baker</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">San Jóse</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-29"><hi rend="italic">April 29,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>After the British occupied Corinto, 27th, town deserted by natives. The
                            Nicaraguan Government stopped railway communication with that port.
                            Pacific Mail steamers have been ordered not to touch there, thus
                            completely isolating town. British seized Government building and
                            archives. Hoisted British flag at that place.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Baker.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>